Class MWE2BaseControllableScheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.evm.api.Scheduler
      • org.eclipse.viatra.emf.mwe2integration.eventdriven.mwe2impl.MWE2BaseControllableScheduler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IController

    public class MWE2BaseControllableScheduler
extends org.eclipse.incquery.runtime.evm.api.Scheduler
implements IController
    An EVM scheduler that enables the workflow to explicitly control the execution of a fine-grained event-driven transformation. As it implements the IController interface, its usage is similar to the MWE2ControllableExecutor. Internally, however, this solution uses a custom Scheduler object instead of an Executor. Using a custom Scheduler means, that the original IncQuery EVM scheduler will be overridden.
    Author:
    Peter Lunk
